<seg id="11">They are expected to shave 0.2 percentage point from annualized consumption growth in the fourth quarter of 2013 and trim an estimated 0.1 percentage point off the annual growth rate of the nation's gross domestic product, according to estimates by Michael Feroli, the chief United States economist at JPMorgan Chase.</seg>
