<seg id="1">Mighty Murray back in fashion</seg>
<seg id="2">Finesse model Charlie surveys one of the most amazing landscapes in the country.</seg>
<seg id="3">Picture: Jody Pachniuk Source: The Advertiser</seg>
<seg id="4">FOR years, Kangaroo Island has been South Australia's biggest drawcard - but that may be about to change.</seg>
<seg id="5">The Adelaide* magazine is touting the Murray and Riverland as the region that is making waves thanks to its near-perfect water conditions, stunning vistas and burgeoning food and wine scene.</seg>
<seg id="6">The mighty Murray has always been a serene backdrop to life in South Australia, but change is afoot in the Riverland and a new wave of artisan producers, chefs, winemakers and tourism operators have made the region a great place for a quick getaway.</seg>
<seg id="7">The Adelaide* magazine used stretches of the River Murray just outside of Renmark as a backdrop to its fashion feature in the April Travel edition of the magazine, and included clothes by Berri designer Fur Elise in the local fashion shoot.</seg>
<seg id="8">From staples such as the Overland Corner Hotel near Barmera, which has served thirsty travellers since 1859, to newcomers like the Pike River eco villas outside Renmark, the region is bursting with good food and accommodation.</seg>
<seg id="9">It's easy to get a taste for the region at the Riverland Farmers Market every Saturday in Berri, where some astonishingly good capers, preserved in River Murray salt, should make it into any shopper's basket.</seg>
<seg id="10">Or visitors can stop in at the Woolshed brewery on the Wilkadene homestead for some Amazon Ale.</seg>
<seg id="11">Banrock Station, which is one of the original tourist destinations along the river, is serving up delicious dishes with a Riverland twist - such as citrus salted crackling on pork.</seg>
<seg id="12">The annual Travel Edition of the Adelaide* magazine is filled with the best the state has to offer travellers.</seg>
<seg id="13">Do not miss your free copy in The Advertiser on Thursday.</seg>
