<seg id="3">THEY are the best of the best in a city that prides itself on hospitality, service and a beer with a view.</seg>
<seg id="4">But is your favourite watering hole in the top 10?</seg>
<seg id="5">The list of Sydney's top ten pubs was released this week by the Australian Hospitality Association NSW after independent judges carried out enviable "painstaking research" at hundreds of establishments over the course of a few months.</seg>
<seg id="6">They nominated 10 of the best pubs from across the city for Best Overall Hotel, with the winner to be announced a gala function on November 25.</seg>
<seg id="7">The top 10 pubs in Sydney include eastern suburbs favourites like the Coogee Bay Hotel and the Clovelly Hotel, the north shore's The Oaks and Willoughby Hotels and inner city pubs including The Clock Hotel , Le Pub and Establishment Hotel.</seg>
<seg id="8">The Oaks at Neutral Bay has one of the best beer gardens in Sydney.</seg>
<seg id="9">Sydney's outer suburbs have not been neglected, with nods going to the Bella Vista Hotel, Fairfield Hotel and Hotel Pennant Hills.</seg>
<seg id="10">Pubs in the running were selected based on key criteria including the standard of their retail liquor outlet, food services, bar presentation, customer service, community support and overall presentation.</seg>
<seg id="11">Aside from best overall pub in Sydney, the awards honour the best boutique bar, best redeveloped hotel, best outdoor area, best family friendly bar and best restaurant.</seg>
<seg id="12">AHA NSW CEO Paul Nicolaou said the finalists were the result of "painstaking research by a team of independent judges and auditors."</seg>
<seg id="13">He said NSW pubs continued to be the best in the country.</seg>
<seg id="14">"NSW hotels are second to none - we see that on display every day," Mr Nicolaou said.</seg>
<seg id="15">Owner Angela Gallagher and Chef Ronny Ghantous from Le Pub in Sydney CBD.</seg>
