<seg id="1">Former Ports Minister Joe Tripodi turns from witness to the subject of ICAC investigation in Circular Quay inquiry</seg>
<seg id="2">Former ALP powerbroker Joe Tripodi fronts the ICAC today.</seg>
<seg id="3">Picture: Ross Schultz Source: News Limited</seg>
<seg id="4">JOE Tripodi, now officially under the corruption watchdog's microscope, says he "didn't like" a change in policy for Circular Quay that ultimately benefited his "mentor" Eddie Obeid.</seg>
