<seg id="12">With McDermott, now returned to his post as Test bowling coach, watching from the stands, Hilfenhaus got his season off to a handy start.</seg>
<seg id="13">If the opportunity pops up I'm more than happy to take it.</seg>
<seg id="14">"I'm just concentrating on playing well for Tassie at the moment and finding some rhythm and hopefully take a few wickets along the way," said Hilfenhaus, who said he's gradually bowling up his loads to be able to reach the 150km speeds he achieved two summers ago.</seg>
<seg id="15">McDermott said Hilfenhaus was certainly in the running for the Ashes.</seg>
<seg id="16">He's quite capable, he's not too old.</seg>
