<seg id="1">Kate Winslet Stars in "Labor Day"</seg>
<seg id="2">On the first day of filming "Labor Day," her new movie, Kate Winslet had a chat with Gattlin Griffith, the 14-year-old actor playing her son.</seg>
<seg id="3">"He was terrified," she recalled.</seg>
<seg id="4">"I just said to him, "You're really nervous, aren't you?""</seg>
<seg id="5">"And I said, "If it's any consolation, so am I and so is Josh, and that" - here she used a robustly off-color noun - "over there, he's the most terrified of them all." " (Josh was Josh Brolin, Ms. Winslet's co-star; the other person across the way was Jason Reitman, the director.)</seg>
<seg id="6">She started relatively young herself, with no formal training, and was just 19 when she delivered an electrifying performance as a New Zealand teenager whose fevered passion propels her into a terrible crime in the 1994 film "Heavenly Creatures."</seg>
<seg id="7">She has since played a careerful of interesting characters, including a spoiled rich girl ("Titanic"), a haunted former Nazi ("The Reader"), a troubled suburban wife ("Revolutionary Road"), a free spirit in and out of love ("Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind") and the young Iris Murdoch ("Iris").</seg>
<seg id="8">But she knows how it feels to learn on the job and also how it feels to be overwhelmed.</seg>
<seg id="9">"I know this age very well," Ms. Winslet continued, speaking of her young co-star.</seg>
<seg id="10">They have a billion questions every day, and they don't know who the hell to ask.</seg>
<seg id="11">I wanted him to know that he could ask me what was going on at any time.</seg>
<seg id="12">It was September, and Ms. Winslet had just introduced "Labor Day," a romance of sorts based on a 2009 Joyce Maynard novel, to an audience at a screening in a Manhattan hotel.</seg>
<seg id="13">During a free hour, she bounded into a meeting room, as much as anyone who is very pregnant and wearing very spiky stilettos can bound.</seg>
<seg id="14">"Do you mind if I take my shoes off?" she asked.</seg>
<seg id="15">Fizzing with energy, her blond hair in a ponytail, her stomach round and her skin glowing, she was dressed all in black - stretchy top, pants and a fetching tuxedo jacket.</seg>
<seg id="16">Meeting Ms. Winslet is a slightly disorienting experience.</seg>
<seg id="17">On the one hand, she is disarming, so instantly intimate, so easy and cozy.</seg>
<seg id="18">On the other hand, she is so deadly serious about her job.</seg>
